I made it to Chongqing, China!! With a population of 36 million (yes, you read that right ‚Äì 36 million!), Chongqing is a municipality that feels more like its own country. This city is massive and chaotic with futuristic skyscrapers and bustling street markets. It‚Äôs one of the most affordable big cities in the world and there‚Äôs something here for everyone to explore.

In this old-school travel vlog, I‚Äôll take you on an adventure through the heart of Chongqing to meet the locals, try some of the spiciest food (hot pot, anyone?), and uncover the wacky culture that makes Chongqing such a unique destination.

What really stood out to me about Chongqing is how it has all the energy and conveniences of a place like Hong Kong, but with almost ZERO tourists. The culture shock here is real, the people are incredibly kind, and the vibe is unlike any other city I‚Äôve experienced in my travels to all 197 countries.

videosBySubcategory.title: Entering The World's Narrowest City
videosBySubcategory.description:
Welcome to Yanjin, China - the narrowest city in the world!  This place is AWESOME!

More than 100,000 people call this unique city home, living in high-rise buildings along a narrow strip of land between steep mountains and the polluted brown River. It‚Äôs truly mind-blowing to see how Yanjin has adapted to its natural environment, with its residents making the most of every inch of space available. The towering mountains in every direction make it feel as though the city is trapped in a stunning, yet challenging, landscape. In all of my travels, I've never seen anything like this!

Also - this is my first time visiting rural China, and I have to admit, it‚Äôs been a refreshing change from the hustle and bustle of massive cities like Beijing or Shanghai. The slower pace, tight-knit community, and the way life carries on here, despite the obvious limitations, have been truly eye-opening. 

Mainland China is full of surprises, and Yanjin is just one of the many hidden gems that I've discovered on this 18 day trip. Stay tuned for the next five videos in my China series, where I‚Äôll be uncovering even more fascinating and lesser-known places across this incredible country! Woohoo!

Thanks to @littlechineseeverywhere for coming on this adventure with me! She makes awesome content (in English) around China!
